Key Match Events: Toronto was crushed from beyond the three-point line — outscored 66-27 — and gave up far too many easy baskets in transition.
Pre-Game Insights: Coach Darko Rajakovic said he didn't want to have any kind of prejudice or expectations, and just wanted to observe and learn what the new group could bring.
Post-Match Reflections: RJ Barrett said the team didn't play hard enough, and that was top to bottom.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Raptors are starting from scratch with a ton to work on following a 128-104 pasting administered by the Milwaukee Bucks.
Others: The search to find a second unit to back up the newly constituted starting group did not include Davion Mitchell or Chris Boucher.
